.TH "irq_cpu_rmap_add" 9 "irq_cpu_rmap_add" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
irq_cpu_rmap_add \- add an IRQ to a CPU affinity reverse-map
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" irq_cpu_rmap_add
.BI "(struct cpu_rmap *rmap "  ","
.BI "int irq "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "rmap" 12
The reverse-map
.IP "irq" 12
The IRQ number
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This adds an IRQ affinity notifier that will update the reverse-map
automatically.

Must be called in process context, after the IRQ is allocated but
before it is bound with \fBrequest_irq\fP.
